00:30:03.044 --> 00:30:06.724
of a cDNA vaccine. This is the kind of thing that Will

506
00:30:06.784 --> 00:30:10.504
Gilanders has worked on for a long time, and they were designed to specifically be

507
00:30:10.524 --> 00:30:13.864
expressed in epithelial cells. So the antigen was

508
00:30:15.164 --> 00:30:17.604
delivered through a gene gun apparatus,

509
00:30:18.184 --> 00:30:19.264
transcribed

510
00:30:20.524 --> 00:30:24.474
in those cells in the skin. And the antigens we showed a

511
00:30:24.504 --> 00:30:25.844
long time ago were

512
00:30:28.144 --> 00:30:32.024
producing a CD8 T cell response that is completely dependent

513
00:30:32.064 --> 00:30:35.424
upon the DC1. So this is showing a cDNA vaccine

514
00:30:35.744 --> 00:30:39.524
tetramer response in a wild type absent in a Delta 32, the one

515
00:30:39.584 --> 00:30:43.284
missing the DC1s. And if you're missing DC2s, it doesn't do

516
00:30:43.304 --> 00:30:47.264
anything. You still get it. So it's a DC1 specific CD8 T

517
00:30:47.304 --> 00:30:51.048
cell response.You can take a soluble

518
00:30:51.068 --> 00:30:54.908
protein and use this adjuvant, Adjuvants, and this also

519
00:30:54.968 --> 00:30:58.768
is a fairly DC1-dependent immune

520
00:30:58.808 --> 00:31:02.428
response. So these vaccines would be dependent upon the

521
00:31:02.468 --> 00:31:03.008
DC1.

522
00:31:04.188 --> 00:31:08.168
We were a little surprised when we used the same model system and used this

523
00:31:08.288 --> 00:31:08.748
mRNA

524
00:31:09.868 --> 00:31:13.668
LNP OVA expressing vaccine from Inovac that Will Gilanders

525
00:31:13.968 --> 00:31:17.108
had obtained, and we see no loss

526
00:31:17.208 --> 00:31:20.808
of tetramer response in any model system.

527
00:31:21.328 --> 00:31:22.488
Meaning that it doesn't

528
00:31:23.428 --> 00:31:25.508
depend on just a DC1 or a DC2.

529
00:31:28.008 --> 00:31:31.348
We have the Wdfy4 knockout mouse, which I showed you earlier,

530
00:31:31.808 --> 00:31:34.668
can't cross-present even though the DC1s are present.

531
00:31:35.068 --> 00:31:38.408
And again, the tetramer response is

532
00:31:39.028 --> 00:31:39.248
still

533
00:31:40.248 --> 00:31:43.488
very proud. So it doesn't

534
00:31:43.528 --> 00:31:45.878
require WD-dependent cross-presentation.

535
00:31:46.188 --> 00:31:49.208
So the question would be, is there anything that's required?

536
00:31:49.228 --> 00:31:52.568
Maybe muscle cells or macrophages are what are doing it.

537
00:31:52.688 --> 00:31:54.428
So we wanted to test this.

538
00:31:55.268 --> 00:31:57.148
Maybe dendritic cells aren't even required.

539
00:31:57.248 --> 00:31:58.808
So to test that, we

540
00:31:59.768 --> 00:32:03.188
used a system in which CD11c DTR,

541
00:32:04.308 --> 00:32:08.128
if you treat the mice, you can eliminate all the dendritic

542
00:32:08.208 --> 00:32:12.198
cells. These would be the conventional DCs here in a wild type are untreated,

543
00:32:12.828 --> 00:32:16.698
and they disappear after treatment, and then the question is what

544
00:32:16.728 --> 00:32:18.728
happens to the tetramer response?

545
00:32:19.098 --> 00:32:22.618
So if you get rid of all classical dendritic cells through this treatment,

546
00:32:23.158 --> 00:32:25.788
that gets rid of the tetramer response.

547
00:32:25.798 --> 00:32:28.628
So at least we're on solid ground. At least

548
00:32:29.148 --> 00:32:32.918
the response is a dendritic cell-dependent response,

549
00:32:33.248 --> 00:32:35.828
but it doesn't care if it's a DC1 or a DC2.

550
00:32:37.328 --> 00:32:41.168
Now I need to talk about the various ways that you can get antigen on a DC.

551
00:32:41.488 --> 00:32:45.128
I've talked about cross-presentation, where exogenous antigen is captured

552
00:32:45.708 --> 00:32:48.768
and put on, and we're trying to work out the cell biology of that.

553
00:32:49.408 --> 00:32:52.948
If you directly express the antigen in the dendritic cell,

554
00:32:53.328 --> 00:32:56.988
that can go through the TAP-dependent loading in the ER, and you can

555
00:32:57.028 --> 00:33:00.648
express antigen. But there's a third way that's called MHC

556
00:33:00.658 --> 00:33:04.137
dressing, or oftentimes called cross-dressing.

557
00:33:04.708 --> 00:33:06.018
And this

558
00:33:06.968 --> 00:33:10.637
is an unusual mechanism. We're not sure if this is the first

559
00:33:10.668 --> 00:33:14.338
paper, but Mike Bevan, in 2011,

560
00:33:14.928 --> 00:33:18.808
published this paper in "Nature" called "Cross-dressed dendritic cells

561
00:33:18.908 --> 00:33:22.178
drive memory CD8 responses." So, and

562
00:33:23.068 --> 00:33:26.408
I'll talk about what this actually is in a second, but

563
00:33:27.308 --> 00:33:28.188
Stephanie Spranger,

564
00:33:29.708 --> 00:33:33.618
just a couple of years ago, published a paper in which she had discovered

565
00:33:33.788 --> 00:33:37.768
a very unusual tumor that turns out to make lots

566
00:33:37.808 --> 00:33:41.668
of type I interferon. But the way she discovered that tumor is that it

567
00:33:41.708 --> 00:33:45.428
was a tumor that was not dependent.

568
00:33:46.028 --> 00:33:49.908
It could drive a CD8 T cell response independently

569
00:33:49.928 --> 00:33:53.488
of DC1s, using either Batf3 knockout mice or Delta

570
00:33:53.648 --> 00:33:54.008
32.

571
00:33:55.008 --> 00:33:55.848
And so she

572
00:33:57.768 --> 00:34:01.048
moved this issue of cross-dressing from just a

573
00:34:01.108 --> 00:34:03.788
viral response into the tumor arena.

574
00:34:04.868 --> 00:34:08.629
This is a slide generated by Gemini at about 10:35 this

575
00:34:08.688 --> 00:34:08.968
morning,

576
00:34:10.368 --> 00:34:14.089
in which I gave a very extensive prompt to try to make a slide

577
00:34:14.848 --> 00:34:16.808
about what is cross-dressing. So

578
00:34:18.528 --> 00:34:21.828
cross-dressing means that the peptide MHC

579
00:34:21.968 --> 00:34:22.669
complex

580
00:34:23.828 --> 00:34:27.388
starts on another cell and is transferred

581
00:34:27.728 --> 00:34:31.609
to the surface of the dendritic cell by some unknown mechanism,

582
00:34:32.048 --> 00:34:35.028
and people propose various mechanisms.

583
00:34:35.048 --> 00:34:38.169
For us, it doesn't matter exactly what the mechanism is.

584
00:34:38.638 --> 00:34:42.609
Stephanie Spranger's work said that whatever the mechanism is, it's dependent

585
00:34:42.649 --> 00:34:44.018
upon type I interferons.

586
00:34:45.288 --> 00:34:49.169
So we need

587
00:34:49.188 --> 00:34:52.728
DCs, but do we need class I MHC on

