594
00:35:13.308 --> 00:35:16.838
But if you look at the Cre positive flox positive mice,

595
00:35:17.388 --> 00:35:20.948
you can see that most of the dendritic cells have lost their surface

596
00:35:21.008 --> 00:35:24.768
expression of class I. That's this purple bump here, and there's a

597
00:35:24.868 --> 00:35:25.688
few

598
00:35:27.168 --> 00:35:29.308
cells that express a little bit of surface class I.

599
00:35:30.608 --> 00:35:33.528
And that's quantified here. But is that significant?

600
00:35:33.608 --> 00:35:37.508
Well, it is significant. That class I that's missing from those

601
00:35:37.528 --> 00:35:41.408
DCs is a sufficient loss to completely

602
00:35:41.448 --> 00:35:45.228
block a tumor response, a

603
00:35:45.248 --> 00:35:46.788
tetramer response. So I

604
00:35:48.748 --> 00:35:52.128
call this Abelson M OVA. It's a tumor line that we made.

605
00:35:52.948 --> 00:35:56.928
It expresses OVA, and it's a B cell tumor made by Abelson transformation.

606
00:35:57.888 --> 00:36:00.928
So you get this induction of a tetramer,

607
00:36:02.068 --> 00:36:05.908
of a OT1 proliferation, and that indicates that the wild

608
00:36:05.988 --> 00:36:09.308
type DCs can cross-present this material.

609
00:36:09.748 --> 00:36:12.018
If you take away class I from the DCs,

610
00:36:13.608 --> 00:36:17.468
you don't get it. So that means that this loss of class I is sufficient

611
00:36:17.478 --> 00:36:20.828
to kill most authentic cross-presented,

612
00:36:22.528 --> 00:36:26.508
but not for mRNA vaccines. So here's the same mouse, this

613
00:36:26.528 --> 00:36:28.008
guy over here, the

614
00:36:29.108 --> 00:36:30.868
11C Cre across the beta 2M.

