00:38:43.840 --> 00:38:46.480
primes a CD8 T cell? And the answer is

656
00:38:47.300 --> 00:38:51.260
we should care because Bob Schreiber showed that it matters in another setting.

657
00:38:51.720 --> 00:38:53.580
So he had published this paper in

658
00:38:55.160 --> 00:38:56.780
2024, and this was a

659
00:38:59.900 --> 00:39:03.680
substantial amount of work from his trainee, Hussein Sultan.

660
00:39:04.010 --> 00:39:07.740
And what this paper showed was, in a model system

661
00:39:08.200 --> 00:39:08.380
of

662
00:39:09.840 --> 00:39:13.800
peptide-induced vaccination. So he has a class I

663
00:39:14.020 --> 00:39:18.000
and a class II epitope in a tumor that has both class I

664
00:39:18.060 --> 00:39:21.610
and class II neoantigens. And immunization

665
00:39:21.700 --> 00:39:23.070
of the mice

666
00:39:24.020 --> 00:39:26.740
using appropriate levels of peptide

667
00:39:27.940 --> 00:39:30.740
can vaccinate those mice, and they give a clean rejection.

668
00:39:30.780 --> 00:39:34.240
That's what this reject-- Here's the unvaccinated mice,

669
00:39:34.760 --> 00:39:37.100
and if you vaccinate, you can clear the tumor.

