00:42:41.560 --> 00:42:45.540
see the wild type, and when you're primed by either wild

727
00:42:45.640 --> 00:42:49.470
type or only primed by DC2s, those look fairly

728
00:42:49.480 --> 00:42:53.320
similar. But if you're primed by a DC1, you have a

729
00:42:53.400 --> 00:42:57.380
greater expansion of fewer effectors and more

730
00:42:57.440 --> 00:42:57.960
cycling

731
00:42:58.840 --> 00:43:02.772
effectors.And I think it's easier to show

732
00:43:02.812 --> 00:43:03.312
this here,

733
00:43:04.592 --> 00:43:06.812
that the red ones are the effectors.

734
00:43:06.892 --> 00:43:10.612
So you get these effectors, but if you're only

